Happy to help with this selection. As you can tell it is a bit confusing. There are so many choices available. Some of that comes with preferred hardware. So just sit back for a moment and let me do my own choosing. 

First, you have to select a radio. Or you already have one. But the choice should include a radio that will promise to send digital signals. Most of them do. Some have settings for digital, some have ports for digital, some are just hard to get along with. 

Next, you should select a sound card device. There are many available options, which work. My choice is the digirig. See: digirig.net. See that one in the picture, (digirit lite) that is the newest and easiest to set up, and cheapest. 

First go to the store: https://digirig.net/store/.  You should have some Digirig Mobile $49.97, you should have Digirig Lite $39.95. Yes, you should have extras of these. The lite version has a setup of RA-Board only. The Mobile has different setups for CAT, TX-500, RS-232, CI-V, or default. (I know this is confusing. Just have some extra on hand)

Now there are two kinds of cables to purchase. One kind is a regular USB cable. Notice they all have a molded choke on each end. This is very important. Get extras of these. It depends on where these will be used. ANOTHER kind of cable is specific to each radio. They are all listed on this page: https://digirig.net/store/. So what radio will you be using: Yaesu, ICom, Kenwood, Anytone, DIN connector, Audio/PTT Cable, Mobilinkd TNC Cable, alinco, MiniDin8Splitter. Once you find the correct one, just get a few extra. Then you will not have to wait for a 2nd shipment.

I can help you with this if you need. 

You should also purchase the GPS receiver Kit.This really helps with location finding. 

I bet you thought this would be a simple email. Oh, it is simple once you get it up and running. 
